Bring large #pot{} of water with a large pinch of @salt{} to a boil. Mince or
grate the @garlic{4%clove}(minced). Peel and mince the @ginger{2%thumb}(peeled
and minced). Trim and discard the bottom inch from the @asparagus{12%ounce},
then split the asparagus length-wise. Prepare a #medium bowl{} of ice water.

Add the asparagus to the boiling water for ~{2-3%minutes}, until tender, then
remove with a #slotted spoon{} and place in the ice water. Add the
@egg noodles{18%ounce} to the boiling water and cook for ~{2-3%minutes}, or
until al dente. Drain.

In a #small bowl{}, combine the @soy sauce{12%teaspoon} and @honey{2%ounce}.

Cook the pork: Thinly slice the @boneless pork chops{24%ounce} into strips and
season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tablespoon} in
a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Working in batches, add the pork to the
pan and cook for ~{1-2%minutes} per side, until browned. Remove from the pan
and set aside.

Heat another drizzle of oil in the same pan over medium heat. Add the ginger
and garlic to the pan and cook, tossing for about ~{30%seconds}, until
fragrant. Add the noodles, teriyaki sauce, asparagus, and pork to the pan and
toss for ~{2-3%minutes}, until the pork is cooked through. Season with salt
and pepper.

Finish and plate: Serve the pork teriyaki sprinkled with @sesame seeds{2%tablespoon}
and enjoy!